# webhosting197 design system (webhosting197-com-site repo)

This rule encodes the canonical brand tokens for **webhosting197.com** - a Bear LLC product brand offering $197 once, lifetime cloud hosting, hand-picked customers only. The token set is intentionally near-identical to slatepress.co (parent SlatePress brand) - shared brand DNA, distinct product positioning.

The source of truth for these tokens is the `:root` block at the top of `index.html`. If they ever drift, this rule should be updated to match - the live file wins.

## Canonical tokens

```css
:root{
  /* Backgrounds */
  --bg:        #FFFFFF;     /* page canvas - pure white */
  --bg-soft:   #FAFAFA;     /* secondary surface */
  --bg-card:   #F7F7F5;     /* card surfaces, subtle warm tint */

  /* Text */
  --ink:       #1C1B1F;     /* primary text - near-black with subtle warm undertone */
  --ink-soft:  #5C5C66;     /* secondary text */
  --slate:     #85858C;     /* tertiary text */

  /* Borders / rules */
  --rule:      #E8E8E8;     /* default 1px borders */
  --rule-soft: #F0F0F0;     /* subtle dividers */
  --rule-strong:#1C1B1F;    /* emphasized borders (matches --ink) */

  /* Brand blue */
  --blue:      #2563EB;     /* PRIMARY brand blue - logo "/" + primary CTAs */
  --blue-deep: #1D4ED8;     /* hover state */
  --blue-soft: #EFF6FF;     /* tinted backgrounds */

  /* Semantic */
  --emerald:   #059669;     /* success / live-status / scarcity-dot pulse */

  /* Layout */
  --max:       1080px;      /* content max-width */
}
```

## Type stack

**Inter only.** Single sans-serif throughout.

```css
font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;
```

## Cardinal rules for webhosting197-com-site

- **Pure white canvas (`--bg`).** Same Mercury-clean canvas as slatepress.co. Backgrounds step down to `--bg-soft` for alternating sections and `--bg-card` for cards.
- **Brand blue (`--blue` #2563EB) is the one accent.** Logo `/`, primary CTAs, focus rings.
- **`--emerald` is reserved for live-status.** The "founder-remaining" scarcity counter, the pulsing dot indicators, and any "live"/"available" semantic moments. NOT a decorative color.
- **High contrast.** Body text against `--bg` should hit WCAG AAA (7:1 ratio). The `--ink` palette has a subtle warm undertone - matches slatepress.co exactly.
- **No new hex codes.** Drift from slatepress.co tokens is the failure mode. If a token changes here, raise the question whether it should change on slatepress.co too (probably yes - they're sister brands).
- **No gradient buttons, no carousels, no Lorem ipsum, no emoji in production UI.**

## Pricing

webhosting197 has its own product pricing ($197 once, lifetime; Founder cohort cap at 100) - distinct from SlatePress Foundation pricing. No cross-repo pricing-sync rule applies to slatepress.co. The product name itself encodes the price ($197), so any pricing change is also a domain-rebrand problem.

## When designing or reviewing UI in this repo

Defer to the `premium-web-designer` Claude skill. When it fires:
1. Ask "What are we designing today?"
2. On the answer "webhosting197.com" or any edit in this repo, load the tokens above.
3. Apply universal taste principles on top.
4. Produce code that references the brand's variable names (`--blue`, `--ink`, `--bg-card`) directly - never invent token names.
